# shadcn/ui

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for all UI elements. Never use raw HTML elements or other component libraries when a shadcn/ui component is available.

## Initialization

If shadcn/ui is not yet set up in the project, run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding Components

If a required component is not installed, add it before using it:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

Examples:
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add input
npx shadcn@latest add dialog
```

## Usage

- Import components from `@/components/ui/<component-name>`
- Always prefer shadcn/ui primitives over custom-built alternatives
- Check `components/ui/` before adding a component — it may already be installed
